Poignée Licensing Policy

English Version

This project is dual-licensed under the Poignée Community License and a Commercial License.

Core Principle:
Poignée Community License: This free license is for individuals and limited use within organizations.
Individuals can use all Poignée functions, and the content they generate may be used for commercial projects.
Companies/Teams can use the software's standard, out-of-the-box functions.
Commercial License: Required for any internal team deployment, or for any secondary development or modification of the source code.

1. Poignée Community License

Permitted Use for Individuals:
Individuals are granted a free, perpetual right to use all functions of the Poignée software.
Any content, designs, or assets generated by an individual using the software may be used for personal or commercial purposes.

Permitted Use for Organizations (Companies & Teams):
Organizations are permitted to use the standard, unmodified functions of the software as provided.

Strict Prohibitions: Under the Poignée Community License, you are strictly prohibited from the following without a Commercial License:
Internal Team Deployment: Installing, hosting, or operating the software in a manner that allows access by multiple users within an organization simultaneously (e.g., on a shared server or internal cloud).
Code Modification & Secondary Development: Modifying, translating, reverse-engineering, decompiling, or creating derivative works based on the Poignée source code.
Redistribution: Redistributing the software, whether modified or unmodified, as part of another product or service.

2. Commercial License

Mandatory Requirement: You MUST purchase a commercial license for any of the following activities:
Internal multi-user or team deployment.
Any secondary development or modification of the Poignée source code.
Embedding or redistributing Poignée as part of your own commercial offering.
Needing technical support, warranties, or indemnification.

A commercial license provides the legal right to deploy Poignée for internal teams and to modify its source code for your organization's specific needs.

To Obtain a Commercial License: Please contact the Poignée team by email at gainshin.hsiao@mail.mcgill.ca to discuss commercial licensing.

3. Contributions

We welcome community contributions. By submitting a contribution, you agree to grant the project maintainers a perpetual, worldwide, non-exclusive, no-charge, royalty-free, irrevocable license to use, reproduce, and sublicense your contribution under any license, including the Commercial License.

4. Additional Terms

Intellectual Property & UI: The visual and interaction design of Poignée is protected under applicable UI/UX design rights and may not be copied or resold as a derivative product without permission.
Medical & Healthcare Compliance: Poignée is designed for dementia care assistance and family coordination. Users must ensure compliance with local healthcare regulations and privacy laws when handling medical information.

